## Vocal & Silent Shevas

In regards to the realization of shevas, Khan remarks (I.2.5.1.1):

> The shewa (◊©÷∞◊Å◊ï÷º÷∏◊ê) sign (◊ê÷∞) in the Tiberian vocalization system was read either as a vowel or as zero. When shewa was read as vocalic, its quality in the Tiberian tradition was by default the same as that of the pata·∏• vowel sign

This package does **not** consider the quality of the realization of the sheva.
It only determines whether the sheva is a _sheva na'_ (vocal) or _sheva nach_ (silent).

### Edge case

- In the word Ô¨™÷∞◊™÷º÷∑◊ô÷¥◊ù _≈°tayim_ (and variants), the first sheva is technially silent.

This package, however, considers it a _sheva na'_.
